36
00:01:21,680 --> 00:01:24,040
MSE stands for Mean Squared Error.

37
00:01:24,040 --> 00:01:25,880
Its formula looks something like this.

38
00:01:25,880 --> 00:01:28,419
So basically, the mean squared error represents three operations.

39
00:01:28,419 --> 00:01:30,119
First, I need to calculate the error.

40
00:01:30,119 --> 00:01:33,039
This means you subtract the actual label value from the predicted value.

41
00:01:33,039 --> 00:01:35,139
