00:01:45,690 --> 00:01:46,970
And that's what the formula looks like when you put it all together.

49
00:01:46,970 --> 00:01:49,170
But a lot of people might see a 1 over 2N in there.

50
00:01:49,170 --> 00:01:50,830
It's just an extra multiplication by one-half.

51
00:01:50,830 --> 00:01:53,070
Actually, this is just to make the derivative calculation more convenient.

52
00:01:53,070 --> 00:01:54,870
Either way, it doesn't affect the final optimization result.

53
00:01:54,870 --> 00:01:56,790
So, why do we square it?

54
00:01:56,790 --> 00:01:58,610
First off, it's to get rid of the positive and negative signs.

