This is the linear model that we've predicted, right?

58
00:02:04,129 --> 00:02:05,969
And this point here represents the actual value.

59
00:02:05,969 --> 00:02:09,289
So, it's likely that each prediction is a little bit off from the actual value.

60
00:02:09,289 --> 00:02:10,400
Some of these errors are big, and some are small.

61
00:02:10,400 --> 00:02:12,020
If you don't square them,

62
00:02:12,020 --> 00:02:14,840
