00:03:10,280 --> 00:03:11,640
it actually remains constant.

96
00:03:11,640 --> 00:03:13,820
you won't be able to calculate the derivative.

97
00:03:13,820 --> 00:03:17,000
But MSE actually makes an underlying assumption.

98
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:20,280
It assumes that our data is actually Gaussian distributed.

99
00:03:20,280 --> 00:03:21,720
In other words, a normal distribution.

100
00:03:21,720 --> 00:03:25,360
In this case, the majority of the data points are still very close to zero.

101
00:03:25,360 --> 00:03:27,500
